								<p class="headerstyle">Pertinent data:</p>
								<blockquote>
									<p><img src="../../page_elements/content_bullet.gif" width="5" height="5"> <b>General Aspects:</b> It is surrounded by gently rolling hills that are covered with villas and farms, vineyards and orchards. The city became a very important cultural center. The Florentine vernacular became the Italian language; and the local coin, the florin, became a world monetary standard. Italian legendary writers such as Boccaccio and Dante came from Florence.</p>
									<p><img src="../../page_elements/content_bullet.gif" width="5" height="5"> <b>Political Aspects:</b> The political life of a Florentine in the 13th and 14th centuries was usually governed by the party with which one chose to align himself. In the 13th century the two warring factions were called the <a href="../../../history/hist_1.php">Guelfs and the Ghibellines</a>, while in the 14th century the fighting was between the Black and White Guelphs.</p>
									<p><img src="../../page_elements/content_bullet.gif" width="5" height="5"> <b>Cultural Aspects:</b> The 13th century was a time of great cultural flowering for Florence. The economy was booming and much money was spent on the arts and entertainment. Giotto, one of the forefathers of naturalism in painting, flourished during this period.</p>
								</blockquote>
								<p class="headerstyle">Major Locations:</p>
